Key Match Events: David Wiese starred with bat and ball as Namibia beat Oman in the super over.
David Wiese blasted 13 runs in Namibia’s super over total of 21 before then restricting Oman to 10 runs to seal victory.
Ruben Trumpelmann bagged four wickets, including two with his first two balls, as Namibia skittled Oman for 109 all out in 19.4 overs.

Trumpelmann trapped opener Kashyap Prajapati lbw for a golden duck with the first ball of the match, and then followed it up moments later with a toe-crusher to get rid of Oman skipper Aqib Ilyas for a duck.
Trumpelmann claimed his third scalp in the third over, removing Naseem Khushi.
David Wiese took 3-28 off 3.4 overs.
Mehran Khan's stunning bowling performance saw Namibia finish on 109-6 to set up the super over drama.

Pre-Game Insights: Namibia won the toss and opted to bowl first.
Matthew Hayden at the pitch report says that there is a bit of wind coming in from the East coast and in general, the boundaries are small all across the ground.
Eion Morgan says that the pitch will get slower as the game goes on and the pacers will use the slower balls more and more.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match at Kensington Oval went to a super over after a nerve-jangling low-scoring battle which saw Oman bundled out for 109.
Namibia’s run-chase faltered after a stunning bowling performance by Oman’s Mehran Khan saw them finish on 109-6 to set up the super over drama.
